{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa118a1dcf77fb9a7","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"/sc:analyze --seq\n\nREAD-ONLY analysis only. Do not modify any files.\n\nCompare this assigned file against three refactoring release specs to identify whether each item is REDUNDANT, CONTRADICTED, OVERLAPPING, or UNAFFECTED.\n\nShared context:\nThe v3.5RigorFlowMerger improve-*.md files were written BEFORE these three refactoring releases were designed. The refactoring releases may render improve-file items:\n- REDUNDANT: the refactor already implements what the improve item proposes\n- CONTRADICTED: the refactor makes the improve item's target file/system incompatible or replaced\n- OVERLAPPING: partial overlap — the refactor implements some of the item but not all\n- UNAFFECTED: no relationship; item stands independently\n\nReference specs:\n1. /config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md\n2. /config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md\n3. /config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md\n\nAssigned file:\n/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-adversarial-pipeline.md\n\nFor each item in the assigned file (AP-001, AP-002, AP-003), produce:\n\n**ITEM [ID]** — [title]\n- Status: REDUNDANT | CONTRADICTED | OVERLAPPING | UNAFFECTED\n- Evidence: cite specific section/file from which refactor spec(s) create the relationship\n- Recommendation: KEEP-AS-IS | REVISE (describe what changes) | REMOVE (reason)\n\nEnd with one paragraph summarizing the assigned file's overall disposition after the three refactors."},"uuid":"b3c9de75-0b3b-42f3-879e-947b3a421c6b","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:46:48.304Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","v