{"parentUuid":"1edc1dc7-93f8-45a8-b075-3d1250d0d4c1","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa118a1dcf77fb9a7","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_KPkBTSVynFRkHPrxHsxVBwlY","type":"tool_result","content":"   620→def _classify_mechanism(matched_text: str) -> str:\n   621→    \"\"\"Classify matched text into a mechanism category.\"\"\"\n   622→    lower = matched_text.lower()\n   623→    if any(k in lower for k in (\"dispatch\", \"runner\", \"handler\", \"command_map\", \"step_map\")):\n   624→        return \"dispatch_table\"\n   625→    if \"registry\" in lower or \"register\" in lower:\n   626→        return \"registry\"\n   627→    if any(k in lower for k in (\"inject\", \"callable\", \"protocol\", \"factory\", \"provider\")):\n   628→        return \"dependency_injection\"\n   629→    if any(k in lower for k in (\"wire\", \"bind\", \"populate\")):\n   630→        return \"explicit_wiring\"\n   631→    if any(k in lower for k in (\"route\", \"routing\")):\n   632→        return \"routing\"\n   633→    if any(k in lower for k in (\"strategy\", \"concretestrategy\")):\n   634→        return \"strategy_pattern\"\n   635→    if any(k in lower for k in (\"middleware\", \"app.use\", \"pipeline.add\")):\n   636→        return \"middleware_chain\"\n   637→    if any(k in lower for k in (\"emitter\", \"addeventlistener\", \"subscribe\", \"listener\")):\n   638→        return \"event_binding\"\n   639→    if any(k in lower for k in (\"container\", \"injector\", \"dependencycontainer\")):\n   640→        return \"di_container\"\n   641→    return \"integration_point\"\n   642→\n   643→\n   644→def _extract_identifiers(text: str) -> list[str]:\n   645→    \"\"\"Extract UPPER_SNAKE_CASE and PascalCase identifiers from text.\"\"\"\n   646→    # UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (likely constants/tables)\n   647→    upper_snake = re.findall(r'\\b[A-Z][A-Z0-9_]{2,}\\b', text)\n   648→    # PascalCase class names\n   649→    pascal = re.findall(r'\\b[A-Z][a-z]+(?:[A-Z][a-z]+)+\\b', text)\n   650→    return upper_snake + pascal\n   651→```\n   652→\n   653→### Pattern Library Expansion\n   654→\n   655→<!-- Source: V5-1 (integration contract extractor), adapted per refactor-plan Section 6 Weakness 2 -->\n   656→\n   657→The `DISPATCH_PATTERNS` and `WIRING_TASK_PATTERNS` have been expanded beyond V5's original 4+3 patterns to cover all 7 categories from V5's integration mechanism taxonomy:\n   658→\n   659→| Category | DISPATCH_PATTERNS coverage | WIRING_TASK_PATTERNS coverage |\n   660→|---|---|---|\n   661→| Dict dispatch | `DISPATCH_TABLE`, `RUNNERS`, `HANDLERS`, `command_map`, `step_map` | `create/populate dispatch table/map` |\n   662→| Plugin registry | `registry`, `register` | `register implementations into registry` |\n   663→| Callback injection | `Callable`, `Protocol`, `ABC`, `Factory`, `Provider` | `wire/inject handlers into` |\n   664→| Strategy pattern | `Context(strategy=...)`, `Strategy`, `ConcreteStrategy` | `configure strategy` |\n   665→| Middleware chain | `middleware`, `app.use`, `pipeline.add` | `set up middleware chain` |\n   666→| Event binding | `emitter.on`, `addEventListener`, `subscribe` | `configure event binding` |\n   667→| DI container | `container.bind`, `container.register`, `Provider`, `Injector` | `initialize DI container` |\n   668→\n   669→---\n   670→\n   671→## 6. Module 3: Fingerprint Extraction\n   672→\n   673→<!-- Source: V4-2 (fingerprint extraction) -->\n   674→\n   675→### Concept\n   676→\n   677→Goes beyond formal requirement IDs to extract \"structural fingerprints\" -- function names, class names, data structure names, and design pattern names that appear in code fences or backtick-delimited spans in the spec. Verifies each fingerprint appears in the roadmap. This is mechanism-agnostic: it catches any code-level identifier omission regardless of whether the spec uses FR-NNN tags or specific integration patterns.\n   678→\n   679→### Detection Axis\n   680→\n   681→V4-2 has the highest single-check efficacy (95% confidence) because it operates on the exact code-level identifiers that specs contain. A spec that mentions `_run_programmatic_step` in backticks expects the roadmap to plan for that function. If the roadmap does not mention it at all, coverage is objectively incomplete.\n   682→\n   683→### Implementation\n   684→\n   685→**File**: `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/fingerprint.py` (new, ~150 LOC)\n   686→\n   687→```python\n   688→\"\"\"Structural fingerprint extraction and coverage checking.\n   689→\n   690→Extracts code-level identifiers from spec content (backtick-delimited names,\n   691→code-block definitions, ALL_CAPS constants) and verifies a minimum coverage\n   692→ratio appears in the roadmap. Catches wholesale omission of design detail\n   693→that text-matching on formal IDs would miss.\n   694→\n   695→Pure function: content in, result out. No I/O.\n   696→\"\"\"\n   697→\n   698→from __future__ import annotations\n   699→\n   700→import re\n   701→from dataclasses import dataclass\n   702→\n   703→\n   704→@dataclass\n   705→class Fingerprint:\n   706→    \"\"\"A named code-level entity from the spec.\"\"\"\n   707→    text: str           # e.g., \"_run_programmatic_step\"\n   708→    category: str       # \"identifier\", \"definition\", \"constant\"\n   709→    source_context: str # surrounding text for debugging\n   710→\n   711→\n   712→# Common non-specific constants to exclude from fingerprint extraction\n   713→_EXCLUDED_CONSTANTS = frozenset({\n   714→    'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'NONE', 'TODO', 'NOTE', 'WARNING',\n   715→    'HIGH', 'MEDIUM', 'LOW', 'YAML', 'JSON', 'STRICT',\n   716→    'STANDARD', 'EXEMPT', 'LIGHT', 'PASS', 'FAIL',\n   717→    'INFO', 'DEBUG', 'ERROR', 'CRITICAL',\n   718→})\n   719→\n   720→\n   721→def extract_code_fingerprints(content: str) -> list[Fingerprint]:\n   722→    \"\"\"Extract code-level identifiers from spec content.\n   723→\n   724→    Sources:\n   725→    1. Backtick-delimited identifiers: `_run_programmatic_step()`\n   726→    2. Code-fenced blocks: function/class definitions\n   727→    3. ALL_CAPS constants (likely important data structures)\n   728→    \"\"\"\n   729→    fingerprints: list[Fingerprint] = []\n   730→\n   731→    # 1. Backtick identifiers (most reliable)\n   732→    for match in re.finditer(r'`([a-zA-Z_]\\w*(?:\\(\\))?)`', content):\n   733→        text = match.group(1).rstrip('()')\n   734→        if len(text) >= 4:  # skip trivial identifiers\n   735→            ctx_start = max(0, match.start() - 40)\n   736→            ctx_end = min(len(content), match.end() + 40)\n   737→            fingerprints.append(Fingerprint(\n   738→                text=text,\n   739→                category=\"identifier\",\n   740→                source_context=content[ctx_start:ctx_end].replace('\\n', ' '),\n   741→            ))\n   742→\n   743→    # 2. Code block function/class definitions\n   744→    code_block_pat = re.compile(r'```(?:python)?\\n(.*?)```', re.DOTALL)\n   745→    for block_match in code_block_pat.finditer(content):\n   746→        block = block_match.group(1)\n   747→        for def_match in re.finditer(r'(?:def|class)\\s+(\\w+)', block):\n   748→            fingerprints.append(Fingerprint(\n   749→                text=def_match.group(1),\n   750→                category=\"definition\",\n   751→                source_context=def_match.group(0),\n   752→            ))\n   753→\n   754→    # 3. ALL_CAPS constants (likely important data structures)\n   755→    for match in re.finditer(r'\\b([A-Z][A-Z_]{3,})\\b', content):\n   756→        text = match.group(1)\n   757→        if text not in _EXCLUDED_CONSTANTS:\n   758→            fingerprints.append(Fingerprint(\n   759→                text=text,\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"uuid":"548ca45f-5deb-4add-bcde-9bdce4bb23e1","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:47:24.831Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"1edc1dc7-93f8-45a8-b075-3d1250d0d4c1","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
